The paper discusses a mathematical measure of academic performance based on the h-index and the Integrated Impact Indicator (I3), which are commonly used in the field of computer science. The paper also provides examples of its application in the context of journal sets, universities, and individual authors. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), which deals with the organization, management, and retrieval of digital information. Other likely sub-categories include cs.CY (Computational Geometry), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
